Mercari Price Suggestion Challenge¶

Can you automatically suggest product prices to online sellers?

1. Business Understanding¶

It can be hard to know how much somethings really worth. Small details can mean big differences in pricing. For example, one of these sweaters cost 335 dollars and the other cost 9.99 dollars. Can you guess which ones which?

Product pricing gets even harder at scale, considering just how many products are sold online. Clothing has strong seasonal pricing trends and is heavily influenced by brand names, while electronics have fluctuating prices based on product specs.

Mercari, Japans biggest community-powered shopping app, knows this problem deeply. Theyd like to offer pricing suggestions to sellers, but this is tough because their sellers are enabled to put just about anything, or any bundle of things, on Mercari's marketplace.

The goal is to build an algorithm that automatically suggests the right product prices

2. Data Understanding¶

2.1. Data Dictionary¶

Train and test data sets consist of 7 (8 in train set, including target variable) columns, representing following data:

  • train_id or test_id - the id of the listing
  • name - the title of the listing. Note that we have cleaned the data to remove text that look like prices (e.g. 20USD) to avoid leakage. These removed prices are represented as [rm]
  • item_condition_id - the condition of the items provided by the seller
  • category_name - category of the listing
  • brand_name
  • shipping - 1 if shipping fee is paid by seller and 0 by buyer
  • item_description - the full description of the item. Note that we have cleaned the data to remove text that look like prices (e.g. 20USD) to avoid leakage. These removed prices are represented as [rm]
  • price - the price that the item was sold for. This is the target variable that you will predict. The unit is USD. This column doesn't exist in test.tsv since that is what you will predict.

In [479]:
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 7))
x = np.arange(1, 6, 1)
y1 = X_train.join(y_train).groupby("item_condition_id")["price"].mean() 
y2 = X_train.join(y_train).groupby("item_condition_id")["price"].median()

bars1 = ax.bar(x-0.2,
               y1,
               width=0.4, color="mediumorchid", label="Mean price", edgecolor="black")
bars2 = ax.bar(x+0.2,
               y2,
               width=0.4, color="skyblue", label="Median price", edgecolor="black")

ax.set_title("Mean and median price for different item condition", fontsize=20, pad=15)
ax.set_ylabel("Price", fontsize=15, labelpad=15)
ax.set_xlabel("Item condition id", fontsize=15, labelpad=10)
ax.tick_params(axis="x", labelsize=13)
ax.tick_params(axis="y", labelsize=13)
ax.bar_label(bars1, [str(round(x, 2)) for x in y1], padding=3, fontsize=13)
ax.bar_label(bars2, [str(round(x, 2)) for x in y2], padding=3, fontsize=13)
ax.grid(axis="y")
ax.margins(0.05, 0.1)
ax.legend(fontsize=13)
plt.show();

3.1. Dealing with missing values¶

In [483]:
def dealing_with_missing_values(input_data):
    input_data.fillna({'item_description':'Unknown', 'brand_name':'Unknown', 
                       'category_name':'Unknown/Unknown/Unknown'}, inplace=True)
    return input_data

In [488]:
def category_splitter(input_data):
    
    split_categories = input_data['category_name'].str.split('/', expand=True)
    
    input_data['category_1'] = split_categories[0]
    input_data['category_2'] = split_categories[1]
    input_data['category_3'] = split_categories[2]
    
    input_data.drop(columns=['category_name'], inplace=True)
    
    return input_data

X_train=category_splitter(X_train)

In [499]:
categories = X_train['category_2'].unique()

matching_pairs = {}

def clean_category(category):
    
    cleaned_category = category.replace('&', '')
    cleaned_category = cleaned_category.replace('and', '')
    
    words = cleaned_category.split()
    
    return words

for category in categories:

    words = clean_category(category)
    
    for other_category in categories:
        
        other_words = clean_category(other_category)
        
        if other_category == category or (other_category, category) in matching_pairs:
            continue
        
        if any(word in other_words for word in words):
   
            matching_pairs[(category, other_category)] = True

for pair in matching_pairs:
    print(pair)

In [502]:
def same_categories_mapping(input_data):
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Tops', 'category_2'] = 'Tops & Blouses'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Toy', 'category_2'] = 'Toys'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Books and Zines', 'category_2'] = 'Book'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Home Decor', 'category_2'] = 'Home Dcor'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Paper Ephemera', 'category_2'] = 'Paper Goods'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Sweats & Hoodies', 'category_2'] = 'Sweaters'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Footwear', 'category_2'] = 'Shoes'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Bathing & Skin Care', 'category_2'] = 'Skin Care'
    input_data.loc[input_data['category_2'] == 'Pregnancy & Maternity', 'category_2'] = 'Maternity'
    input_data.loc[(input_data['category_2'] == 'Suits') |
                   (input_data['category_2'] == 'Blazers & Sport Coats'), 'category_2'] = 'Suits & Blazers'
    input_data.loc[(input_data['category_2'] == '') |
                   (input_data['category_2'] == 'Blazers & Sport Coats'), 'category_2'] = 'Suits & Blazers'
    
    return input_data

Mozemo dakle ili

  • napraviti binarnu promenljivu ima ili nema brend poznat kupcu
  • ili izabrati top 30 brendova

Sa 30 od 4650 varijabli zadrzali bismo samo 51% varijabiliteta medju instancama koje imaju brend, dok na ukupnom skupu samo 29% varijabli ima jedan od top 30 brendova

Dodatno, mozemo primetiti da su uglavnom jako poznati tj luksuzniji brednovi ti koji su zastupljeni na listi top 30, to ukazuje da samo postojanje brenda nosi sa sobom uglavnom viu cenu, pa nam binarna varijabla moe biti u ovom sluaju i te kako korisna.

Za kolonu item description cemo tamo gde nema vrednost upisati kolonu name, i to zbog:

    1. item_description kolona informativnija od same name kolone, ali u nedostatku iste i name ce nam biti informativan (name je uglavnom skracena verzija item description kada oba postoje)
    1. name nema missing values
    1. cak 5% trening skupa nemamo description (No description yet), a to je najzastupljenija kategorija
    1. a i da smo za tu kolonu upisivali Unknown gde nam je vrednost bila NaN.

In [536]:
def remove_emoji(sentence):
    pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return pattern.sub(r'', sentence)
In [537]:
def remove_punctuation(sentence):
    regular_punct = list(string.punctuation)
    for punc in regular_punct:
        if punc in sentence:
            sentence = sentence.replace(punc, ' ')
    return sentence.strip()
In [538]:
porter_stemmer = PorterStemmer()
def stemming(text):
    input_str=word_tokenize(text)
    res = [porter_stemmer.stem(word) for word in input_str]
    return ' '.join(res)

In [541]:
def process_text(input_data, col):
    processed_data = []
    for sentence in input_data[col].values:
            sent = sentence
            sent = sent.replace('\\r', ' ') #sklanja escape karakter, prelazak kursova ali ne u novi red
            sent = sent.replace('\\"', ' ') #sklanja dvosturke navodnike
            sent = sent.replace('\\n', ' ') #sklanja enter
            sent = re.sub('[^A-Za-z]+', ' ', sent) #sklanja sva slova koja nisu alfabet tj engleska abeceda
            sent = remove_emoji(sent)
            sent = remove_punctuation(sent)
            sent = ' '.join(e for e in sent.split() if e not in words_to_exclude)
            sent = stemming(sent)
            processed_data.append(sent.lower().strip())  
    input_data[col] = processed_data
    return input_data

In [261]:
def get_text_encodings(input_data, col_name, min_val, max_val):
    vect_tr = CountVectorizer(ngram_range=(min_val, max_val), max_features=10, min_df=250000)
    vect_tr.fit(input_data[col_name]) 

    input_data_encoded = pd.DataFrame(vect_tr.transform(input_data[col_name]).todense(), 
                                      columns=vect_tr.get_feature_names_out())

    input_data_encoded.index = input_data.index
    
    return input_data_encoded

4.1. Pipeline for data cleaning¶

In [71]:
from sklearn.base import BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin

class MissingValuesHandler(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('1 - MissingValuesHandler')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        X_transformed.fillna({'item_description':'Unknown', 'brand_name':'Unknown', 
                  'category_name':'Unknown/Unknown/Unknown', 'name':'Unknown'}, inplace=True)
        
        X_transformed['shipping'].fillna(X_transformed['shipping'].median(), inplace=True)
        X_transformed['item_condition_id'].fillna(X_transformed['item_condition_id'].median(), inplace=True)
        
        return X_transformed

class CategorySplitter(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('2 - CategorySplitter')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        split_categories = X_transformed['category_name'].str.split('/', expand=True)
        X_transformed['category_1'] = split_categories[0]
        X_transformed['category_2'] = split_categories[1]
        X_transformed.drop(columns=['category_name'], inplace=True)
        
        return X_transformed

class SameCategoryMapper(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('3 - SameCategoryMapper')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
            
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Tops', 'category_2'] = 'Tops & Blouses'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Toy', 'category_2'] = 'Toys'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Books and Zines', 'category_2'] = 'Book'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Home Decor', 'category_2'] = 'Home Dcor'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Paper Ephemera', 'category_2'] = 'Paper Goods'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Sweats & Hoodies', 'category_2'] = 'Sweaters'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Footwear', 'category_2'] = 'Shoes'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Bathing & Skin Care', 'category_2'] = 'Skin Care'
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Pregnancy & Maternity', 'category_2'] = 'Maternity'
        X_transformed.loc[(X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Suits') | 
        (X_transformed['category_2'] == 'Blazers & Sport Coats'), 'category_2'] = 'Suits & Blazers'
    
        return X_transformed

class Top40CategoriesKeeper(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('4 - Top40CategoriesKeeper')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        top_categories =  X_transformed['category_2'].value_counts()[:40].index.tolist()
        
        X_transformed.loc[~X_transformed['category_2'].isin(top_categories), 'category_2'] = 'Unknown'
    
        return X_transformed

class BrandEncodeer(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('5 - BrandEncodeer')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        X_transformed['brand_flag'] = X_transformed['brand_name'].apply(lambda x: 0 if x == 'Unknown' else 1)
        
        top_brands = X_transformed['brand_name'].value_counts()[:11].index.tolist()
        X_transformed.loc[~X_transformed['brand_name'].isin(top_brands), 'brand_name'] = 'Unknown'
    
        return X_transformed
    
class NoDescriptionImputer(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('6 - NoDescriptionImputer')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['item_description'] == 'Unknown' , 'item_description'] = 'No description yet'
   
        X_transformed.loc[X_transformed['item_description'] == 'No description yet', 'item_description'] = X_transformed['name']
        X_transformed.drop(columns=['name'], inplace=True)
    
        return X_transformed    
    
class EmptyTransfomer(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
    
        return X 
    
pipeline_for_data_cleaning = Pipeline(steps=[
    ('missing_values_handler', MissingValuesHandler()),  # Custom transformer to handle missing values
    ('category_splitter', CategorySplitter()), # Custom transformer to split category_name
    ('category_2_mapper', SameCategoryMapper()), # Custom transformer to map the same categories
    ('category_2_top40', Top40CategoriesKeeper()), # Custom transformer to keep only top 40 categories in category 2
    ('brand_flag', BrandEncodeer()), # Custom transformer to make flag for brand column
    ('no_description_imputer', NoDescriptionImputer()),  # Custom transformer to impute description by name where it is needed
    ('empty_transformer', EmptyTransfomer())
])

4.2. Pipeline for NLP¶

In [72]:
def remove_emoji(sentence):
    pattern = re.compile("["
                           u"\U0001F600-\U0001F64F"
                           u"\U0001F300-\U0001F5FF"
                           u"\U0001F680-\U0001F6FF"
                           u"\U0001F1E0-\U0001F1FF"
                           u"\U00002702-\U000027B0"
                           u"\U000024C2-\U0001F251"
                           "]+", flags=re.UNICODE)
    return pattern.sub(r'', sentence)
In [73]:
def remove_punctuation(sentence):
    regular_punct = list(string.punctuation)
    for punc in regular_punct:
        if punc in sentence:
            sentence = sentence.replace(punc, ' ')
    return sentence.strip()
In [74]:
porter_stemmer = PorterStemmer()
def stemming(text):
    input_str=word_tokenize(text)
    res = [porter_stemmer.stem(word) for word in input_str]
    return ' '.join(res)

In [76]:
def nlp_function(sent):
    sent = sent.replace('\\r', ' ') #sklanja escape karakter, prelazak kursova ali ne u novi red
    sent = sent.replace('\\"', ' ') #sklanja dvosturke navodnike
    sent = sent.replace('\\n', ' ') #sklanja enter
    sent = re.sub('[^A-Za-z]+', ' ', sent) #sklanja sva slova koja nisu alfabet tj engleska abeceda
    sent = remove_emoji(sent)
    sent = remove_punctuation(sent)
    sent = ' '.join(e for e in sent.split() if e not in words_to_exclude)
    sent = stemming(sent)
    sent= sent.lower().strip()
    return sent
In [77]:
class TextProcessor(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('1 - TextProcessor')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
     
        clean_item_description = X_transformed['item_description'].apply(nlp_function)
    
        X_transformed['item_description'] = clean_item_description
        
        return X_transformed

class NewColumnsGenerator(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):

    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self

    def transform(self, X):
        print('2 - NewColumnsGenerator')
        
        X_transformed=X.copy()
        
        X_transformed['new_flag'] = X_transformed['item_description'].str.contains(r'\bnew\b', case=False, na=False).astype(int)
        X_transformed['size_flag'] = X_transformed['item_description'].str.contains(r'\bsize\b', case=False, na=False).astype(int)
        X_transformed.drop(columns=['item_description'], inplace=True)
            
        
        return X_transformed
        
pipeline_for_nlp = Pipeline(steps=[
    ('text_preprocessor', TextProcessor()), # Custom transformer to handle NLP
    ('new_columns_generator_from_desc',  NewColumnsGenerator()), # Custom transformer to create columns of repetitive words
    ('empty_transformer', EmptyTransfomer()) #Empty transformer just for cheating
])

In [85]:
def rmse_score(y_true, y_predict):
    diff = y_true-y_predict
    diff_squared = np.power(diff,2)
    mse = diff_squared.mean()
    rmse = np.sqrt(mse)
    return(rmse)
In [86]:
def RMSLE_loss(actual,predictions):
    actual = np.expm1(actual)
    predictions = np.expm1(predictions)
    loss = np.sqrt(np.power(np.log(predictions + 1) - np.log(actual + 1),2).mean())
    return (loss)

4.4. Final Pipeline - LightGBM¶

In [52]:
import re
import lightgbm as lgb
from lightgbm import LGBMRegressor
from scipy import sparse
In [53]:
class AttributeRenamer(BaseEstimator, TransformerMixin):
    def fit(self, X, y=None):
        return self
    
    def transform(self, X):
        print('1 - AttributeRenamer')
        
        if isinstance(X, pd.DataFrame):
            
            X_transformed = X.copy()
            X_transformed.columns = [re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9_]+', '', col) for col in X_transformed.columns]
            X_transformed.columns = X_transformed.columns.str.replace('_', '1')
        
        elif sparse.issparse(X):
    
            X_df = pd.DataFrame.sparse.from_spmatrix(X)
            
            X_df.columns = [re.sub('[^A-Za-z0-9_]+', '', col) for col in X_df.columns]
            X_df.columns = X_df.columns.str.replace('_', '1')
            X_transformed=X_df.copy()
    
        
        return X_transformed

Saving the dataset as input for hyperparameter optimisation¶

In [317]:
def get_dataset_after_ohe(my_pipeline,X):
    
    numerical_cols = list(X.select_dtypes(exclude = 'object').columns)
    categorical_cols = list(X.select_dtypes(include = 'object').columns)
    
    X_transformed = my_pipeline.named_steps['preprocessor'].transform(X)
    
    onehot_columns = my_pipeline.named_steps['preprocessor'].named_transformers_['cat'].named_steps['onehot'].get_feature_names_out(categorical_cols)
    
    all_columns = numerical_cols + onehot_columns.tolist()
    
    X_processed = pd.DataFrame.sparse.from_spmatrix(X_transformed, columns=all_columns)
    X_processed = X_processed.sparse.to_dense()
    
    return X_processed

X_novo=get_dataset_after_ohe(opt_pipeline_tree,X_train_trying)
